<exercise id="fs-id1172101881452">
<problem id="fs-id1172102142809">
<para id="fs-id1172102145294">An ideal gas expands quasi-statically to three times its original volume. Which process requires more work from the gas, an isothermal process or an isobaric one? Determine the ratio of the work done in these processes.</para>
